The paper deals with defending deep learning models against adversarial attacks in image classification tasks, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using multiple color spaces in the same model, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to improve model performance. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in defending against various types of adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to feature extraction, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE).
